  <title translate="true">Tip #7</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Dolphin is written almost entirely in itself, and is supplied with full source code. As you become more familiar with the image you will find it a mine of useful code and techniques.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Learning to browse the image successfully is a very important skill for getting the most out of Smalltalk. If you want to learn how a piece of code works use the </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/References to </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">(Shift+F12)</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Method/Definitions of</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">(F12) commands to find out where other methods are used and defined.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
